00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:34,100
your grandfather had already
begun making preparations!

151
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:39,480
He devised a plan to poison
those irksome daimyo one by one!

152
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:45,150
He got rid of them one after another,
making them all look like inside jobs!

153
00:07:45,150 --> 00:07:49,160
The series of daimyo deaths was
too much for the shogun,

154
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:51,910
and he eventually took ill.

155
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,660
His plan had been flawless!

156
00:07:54,660 --> 00:08:00,250
But just as he was within
reach of seizing power...

157
00:08:02,590 --> 00:08:04,960
that brat was born...!

158
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:08,680
The heir, Kozuki Sukiyaki!

159
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:11,220
– Yes!
– Yes!

160
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:13,310
Congratulations!

161
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:18,390
A curse on you, Sukiyaki!

162
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:22,060
He was only one step away from power,

163
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:26,240
and to make matters worse,
his plan was exposed!

164
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:30,490
Your grandfather committed seppuku,
and the clan was removed from power!

165
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:34,490
Their territory, castle,
and power were all taken away.

166
00:08:34,490 --> 00:08:37,000
People grew to despise the Kurozumi name,

167
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:41,250
and the members of the clan
ended up on the streets!

168
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:43,960
Whose fault could that be?!

169
00:08:45,340 --> 00:08:48,880
Who was it that made your life so miserable?!

170
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:52,050
Who's responsible for your poverty?!

171
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,930
Upon whom does the blame fall?!

172
00:08:56,890 --> 00:08:58,350
It's because he was birthed!

173
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:02,100
Kozuki Sukiyaki!

174
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,270
That's right!

175
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:09,070
If he had never been born,
you would have one day become shogun!

176
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:12,660
My lord, Shogun!

177
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:14,080
I love you!

178
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,040
My lord, Shogun!

179
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,500
I love you!

180
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:20,920
My lord, Shogun!

181
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:20,920
My lord, Shogun!

182
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:20,920
My lord, Shogun!

183
00:09:22,170 --> 00:09:23,210
What beauties!

184
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:26,090
I'd have...

185
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,670
become shogun?!

186
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:29,470
That's right!

187
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:32,550
Oh, how aggravating! How galling!

188
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:35,930
Don't tell me you're my...

189
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:39,850
That is to say, a fellow Kurozumi?

190
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:43,020
It doesn't matter who I am!

191
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,190
I was out of the country all this time.

192
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,400
It was quite the ordeal...

193
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:51,320
But watch my face.

194
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:53,240
What?!

195
00:09:54,780 --> 00:09:56,080
What?!

196
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,740
Is that my face?!

197
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:04,500
It's the power of the Clone-Clone Fruit.

198
00:10:06,210 --> 00:10:11,550
Should you follow my instructions,
I'm willing to bestow upon you a power of your own.

199
00:10:12,010 --> 00:10:14,720
You'll need this power
if you're to become shogun!

200
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:18,100
I'll...! I'll do anything!

201
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:23,940
Then begin hoarding money
and manufacturing weapons.

202
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:27,270
Wano's craftsmen are incredibly skilled!

203
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:31,740
With them as bait, I'm sure
you can lure in some big-time backers!

204
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:34,200
I understand!

205
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:51,510
Hakumai

206
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,510
My name is Orochi.

207
00:10:51,510 --> 00:10:54,340
My whole family has fallen ill,

208
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:59,390
so I must find a way to feed all of them...

209
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:02,270
That is most unfortunate.

210
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:03,640
Work for me.

211
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,940
A Month

Later

212
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:07,940
Lord Yasuie!

213
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:10,730
What? Orochi has disappeared?

214
00:11:10,730 --> 00:11:11,440
Yes, sir.

215
00:11:12,110 --> 00:11:15,740
And while it is likely just a coincidence,

216
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:18,070
the money in the safe is gone, too.

217
00:11:18,070 --> 00:11:19,450
What?

218
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:22,120
The money is gone, too?

219
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:26,210
Kuri

220
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:29,170
You are that fellow from Yasu's place...

221
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:30,750
My name is Orochi!

222
00:11:31,170 --> 00:11:34,170
I owe Lord Yasuie so much,

223
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:36,260
so I can't borrow money from him!

224
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:39,390
I understand. You can count on me!

225
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,680
You have my gratitude!

226
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:40,600
Lord Oden?!

227
00:11:44,850 --> 00:11:46,390
Lend me money!

